cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for classification of Alzheimer Disease using structural Magnetic Resonance Imaging (sMRI) as the imaging modality. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also touches upon the potential for early detection of Alzheimer Disease, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
